<p> I am an assistant professor at the University of Southern California. My main interests are in metaphysics, epistemology, the philosophy of language and philosophical logic. My most recent work focuses on issues relating to probabilities of conditionals, vagueness and the semantic paradoxes. I am currently writing a book on vagueness entitled "Vagueness and Thought".</p>

